FileHeader.UserComment:
DG - File content must be set to all 'FF' if data generation is required for UPP
Two keys must be personalized in the following way
Key Version 03
03 28 04 12 85 10 $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ (ISD_TLS_PSK) - Pre-Shared Key 05 12 80 10 $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ $$ (RAMDOM 3DES)
It must be derivated as follows:
The input data for PSK calculation is: - The value (data) is the 8 last bytes of the swapped ICCID - The Master Key (KM0) is a 16-byte key.
The algorithm for calculating diversified keys is: KM0 = K1 || K2 KM1 = K2 || K1 R1 = 3-DESKM0(data) R2 = 3-DESKM1(data)
ISD_TLS_PSK = R1 || R2
Where: - K1 = Left-most 8 bytes of the Master Key - K2 = Right-most 8 bytes of the Master Key The PSK is encrypted using 3DES ECB NO_PADDING and using two different 8 byte keys. The PSK is 16 bytes in length.
PSK Format Example of PSK in bytes array format. This example uses: - ICCID = 89256776274942161783 - Master Key = 13609049388822691132078094990796 Bytes Array Representation - PSK = 06607F6DDF0D3681A62386AE97E47CDD

FileHeader.UserComment:
DG - The IMS Private User ID (IMPI) for each UICC contains a valid NAI, and shall be generated according to the following description:
<IMSI>@ims.mnc<MNC>.mcc<MCC>.3gppnetwork.org
User information: <IMSI> - (IMSI for each UICC) Domain-part: @ims.mnc<MNC>.mcc<MCC>.3gppnetwork.org
NOTE: <MNC> and <MCC> are the MNC (padded to the left with a zero, if only a 2-digit MNC) and MCC of a PLMN within the IMSI.
Encoded in NAI TLV form where:
T = 80 L = NAI length V = IMSI (IMSI for this card) + DOMAIN (Domain name used. Claro Argentina uses the default @ims.mnc<MNC>.mcc<MCC>.3gppnetwork.org)
Please see the example for Claro Argentina settings:
722310xxxxxxxxx@ims.mnc310.mcc722.3gppnetwork.org
Content for a IMSI value 722310123456789:
T = 80 L = 31 V = 37323233313031323334353637383940696D732E6D6E633331302E6D63633732322E336770706E6574776F726B2E6F7267

FileHeader.Name: EF LF
FileHeader.UserComment:
DG - Each record of the IMS Public User ID (IMPU) is able to hold a public SIP Identity (SIP URI) ofthe user: The first record (Rec 01) shall contain a dynamic value generated as follows:
sip:<IMSI>@ims.mnc<MNC>.mcc<MCC>.3gppnetwork.org
User information: <IMSI> - (IMSI for each UICC) Domain-part: @ims.mnc<MNC>.mcc<MCC>.3gppnetwork.org
NOTES:
- sip: Fixed string "sip:"
- <MNC> and <MCC> are the MNC (padded to the left with a zero, if only a 2-digit MNC) and MCC of a PLMN within the IMSI;
Encoded in URI TLV form where:
T = 80 L = SIP URI length V = sip: + IMSI (IMSI for this card) + DOMAIN (Domain name used. Claro Argentina uses the default @ims.mnc<MNC>.mcc<MCC>.3gppnetwork.org)
Please see the example for Claro Argentina settings:
sip:722310xxxxxxxxx@ims.mnc310.mcc722.3gppnetwork.org
Content for a IMSI value 722310123456789:
T = 80 L = 35 V = 7369703A37323233313031323334353637383940696D732E6D6E633331302E6D63633732322E336770706E6574776F726B2E6F7267
The remaining records of the IMPU file shall contain the fixed value: 0x 80 00 FF FF FF...
